  "faqQ1": "How do I register my household?",
  "faqA1": "Tap \"Start New Registration\" on the welcome screen. Complete the 4 steps: personal info, identity verification, and membership selection. You can register offline — data syncs when you connect.",
  "faqQ2": "What is a FAN Number?",
  "faqA2": "FAN stands for Fayda Authentication Number — your 12-digit Ethiopian National ID number. You can find it on your Fayda ID card.",
  "faqQ3": "How do I pay my premium?",
  "faqA3": "Tap \"Renew Coverage\" on the Home screen. You can pay via Telebirr, CBE Birr, Amole, HelloCash, or bank transfer through the Chapa payment page.",
  "faqQ4": "How do I add family members?",
  "faqA4": "Go to the Family tab and tap \"Add beneficiary\". You need to capture a photo and provide basic details. Non-child members need a phone number for independent access.",
  "faqQ5": "How do I use my digital CBHI card?",
  "faqA5": "Go to the Card tab to view your digital membership card with QR code. Show this to health facility staff to verify your eligibility for services.",
  "faqQ6": "What if I have no internet connection?",
  "faqA6": "The app works offline. Registration and changes are saved locally and sync automatically when you reconnect. Look for the \"Offline queue active\" indicator on the Home screen.",
  "faqQ7": "How do I track my claims?",
  "faqA7": "Go to the Claims tab to see all claims submitted by health facilities on your behalf. You will see the status (Submitted, Under Review, Approved, Paid, or Rejected).",
  "faqQ8": "How do I find accredited health facilities?",
  "faqA8": "Go to the Facilities tab and search by name. All listed facilities are accredited by EHIA and accept your CBHI membership card.",
  "faqQ9": "Who do I contact for help?",
  "faqA9": "Contact the Ethiopian Health Insurance Agency (EHIA) at info@ehia.gov.et or visit your local CBHI office. You can also call the EHIA helpline.",

